        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend Tool could easily integrate with PHPUnit for Project based testing. Currently zf create project creates some testing related resources, but they are not used.\r\n\r\n1. Remove application\/ and library\/ distinction they dont pair with how PHPUnit works\r\n2. Add a folder tests in each module, i.e. \"modules\/blog\/tests\", \"modules\/guestbook\/tests\".\r\n3. Add two phpunit.xml one called unittest.xml, one functional.xml in the APP_ROOT\/tests\/ mainfolder, they both configure bootstrapFile=\"\" a specific unit-test bootstrap file.\r\n4. Add a AllFunctionalTests TestSuite in APP_ROOT\/tests which detects all tests in folders and subfolders of all module tests\/ folders (functionality is in phpunit already via Glob or something.)\r\n5. Add a AllTests File which includes the AllFunctionalTests\r\n6. Add a Bootstrap File that somehow gathers all autoloader specific resources (is that possible Matthew?!)\r\n\r\nBig advantages:\r\n* Functional tests reside in the module they belong too, yet they are aggregated by a specific TestSuite mechanism.\r\n* We use PHPUnit functionality to gather the unittests, so we don't need to rely on our own additional mechanism (KISS!)\r\n\r\nThe following commands are now available:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nzf run test\r\nzf run test.(functional|unit) <optional:moduleName>\r\nzf create test.functional <controllerName> <optional:moduleName>\r\n{code}"
        },
